cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on parsing and deep multi-task learning suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The use of multiple treebanks and parameter sharing suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of benchmark datasets and experiments suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often involves similar evaluation methods.
